# Frontend Component Conventions

## SharedBackground + ThemedSection

`SharedBackground` wraps children in `<div className="overlay">` and applies:
```css
section:not(.overlay) { background: transparent; }
```
This means any `ThemedSection` inside a `SharedBackground` is **automatically transparent** — its background color is overridden. To keep a section's background, pass `className="overlay"` to `ThemedSection`.

## ThemedSection Padding

`ThemedSection` applies padding via the `width` prop:
- `width="large"` → `padding: 7%` desktop, `padding: 20px` tablet
- `width="medium"` → `padding: 13%` desktop, `padding: 20px` tablet

**The tablet reset (`20px`) lives inside `StyledSection`, but `additionalStyles` is injected AFTER it — so any `padding` in `additionalStyles` overrides the tablet reset.**

✅ Safe — doesn't fight tablet reset:
```js
// Override only top/bottom inside a tablet() block in additionalStyles
${tablet(css`
  padding-top: 60px;
  padding-bottom: 60px;
`)}
```

❌ Dangerous — kills tablet reset:
```js
// Flat padding in additionalStyles overrides the tablet 20px
padding: 60px 13%;
```

## CSS Specificity in Media Queries

Media queries do not increase specificity. A modifier class like `.reversed` (0,2,0) will beat a media query rule targeting the base class (0,1,0) even if the media query comes later.

✅ Fix: repeat the modifier inside the media query:
```css
${tablet(css`
  flex-direction: column;
  &.reversed {
    flex-direction: column; /* same specificity, declared later = wins */
  }
`)}
```

## Button Pattern

There is no standalone Button component. Use a plain `<button>` styled in the section's `additionalStyles`, following the `HomeFeaturedProjects` pattern:

```css
button {
  border-color: transparent;
  background-color: ${theme.colors.white};
  padding: 4px 16px;
  cursor: pointer;
  a { font-size: 1.4rem; color: ${theme.colors.darkAccent}; }
}
button:hover {
  background-color: ${theme.colors.darkAccent};
  a { color: ${theme.colors.white}; }
}
```

Before writing new button styles, grep for existing usage: `rg "button" src/Components --type jsx`
